`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The two-source join pattern (`mapQuestBranchToDisplay`) is common in ECS+store architectures: ECS entities answer "what is happening" (which quests are active, at which step), while the Legend State store answers "how much progress" (per-objective counts). Neither source alone is sufficient.
- `useRef` for side-effect tracking in `useActiveQuestsFromECS` follows the React anti-double-fire pattern: compute the display data first, then use a ref to gate the toast so it only fires on the first render where a step becomes completable — not on every subsequent render.
- The `@rn-primitives/slot` JSX parse issue is a recurring test environment problem — any `.tsx` file that imports from `@/components/ui/*` will trigger it. The canonical fix is 4 jest.mock calls at the top of the test file.
